<TITLE> Cell phone firms agree to help listing voters </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, September 24(bdnews24.com) The chief election commissioner Monday asked for assistance from mobile phone companies to make a complete voter list with photographs. ATM Shamsul Huda met top executives of six mobile companies at Election Commission secretariat, who promised to help the EC. "We will start work on the voter list on a massive scale in November. To involve voters in isolated regions of the country, we asked for help from companies in the telecom industry," election commissioner M Sakhawat Hossain told reporters after the meeting. "We asked the electronic media Sunday to help create public awareness about the voter registration with photographs. In a continuation of that, we met the officials of mobile companies and exchanged thoughts on the issue." "Mobile companies have been briefed on how the voters can be engaged through advertisements. Besides, every time the work for the voter list starts in a big city, [the mobile phone companies] have been asked to inform their clients via SMS which areas we will be working in," the commissioner said. bdnews24.
